title: livingRoom_enterDark
---
<<if !has_flag("living_room_lights_on")>>
  Oh my god...
  This house terrifies me in the dark.
  What even is that?!
  Where's the damn light switch?
  <<load_scene "livingRoom_Lightswitch">>
<<elseif has_flag("living_lights_justFlipped")>>
  <<unset_flag "living_lights_justFlipped">>
  Better.
<<elseif has_flag("mable_scared") and !has_flag("mable_found") and !has_flag("mable_monologue")>>
  It looks like Mable ran off.
  She probably got scared by that creep.
  I wonder where she went off to?
  <<set_flag "mable_monologue">>
<<elseif has_flag("mable_monologue") and !has_flag("mable_found")>>
  Where has Mable ran off to?
<<endif>>
===

title: livingRoom_lightSwitch
---
<<set_flag "living_room_lights_on">>
<<set_flag "living_lights_justFlipped">>
<<load_scene "livingRoom">>
===

title: livingRoom_bedroomDoor
---
<<load_scene "bedRoom">>
===

title: livingRoom_cat
---
<<if has_flag("mable_found")>>
  Looks like Mable is feeling okay...
  <<stop>>
<<endif>>
My beautiful cat, Mable.
===

title: livingRoom_kitchen
---
<<load_scene "kitchen">>
